news.title: Ludhiana development body evicts illegal occupiers of three LIG flats in sector-40
news.para: The officials said Glada had built 319 low-income group flats in Sector 40, of which 82 were occupied illegally.

news.title: Kerala: SIT seeks halting of resurvey of puramboke land
news.para: The SIT led by inspector general of police K Sethuraman, constituted as per a high court directive, has submitted a 741-page report to the govt.

news.title: Jaipur: Rampant constructions poses threat to Walled City legacy
news.para: "The regulation stipulates that any construction or modification facing main bazars shall endeavour to maintain the existing architectural volume and character.

news.title: Kolkata HC directs Darjeeling municipality to halt illegal construction on Mall Road
news.para: The municipality clarified that the beautification work and shifting of the hawkers down the extended road is being done by them, and funds are being provided by GTA.

news.title: Permission from police not needed for carrying out construction: Delhi government
news.para: "There is no provision under Delhi Municipal Corporation Act, 1957 by which a person is required to seek permission from police for carrying out construction," the circular read

news.title: Delhi government mandates all high-rise buildings to install anti-smog guns
news.para: Rising pollution was a major election issue in Delhi and the BJP had accused the previous AAP government of failing to check it.

news.title: Drive to regularise constructions in South Goa yields poor results
news.para: The drive, held at all deputy collectors’ offices throughout the district from 10am to 5pm, was attended by applicants and representatives from various govt departments.

news.title: Gujarat government caps transfer fees at Rs 1 lakh for housing societies
news.para: The move aims to prevent housing societies from imposing arbitrary levies on property transfers, a common grievance among homebuyers and sellers.

news.title: RERA project registrations drops 21% between 2022-2024: Report
news.para: According to the report, the registration of projects saw a remarkable 145 per cent growth, reaching 25,281 projects between 2020 and 2022.

news.title: Odisha government to implement sustainable construction methods for housing initiative
news.para: Gangadhar Nayak, mission director of the Odisha Urban Housing Mission (OUHM), confirmed the state's commitment to this environmental initiative in a communication to the Centre.

news.title: Over 1,000 Mysuru development body's sites allotted under 50:50 scheme: Lokayukta report
news.para: Lokayukta has sought the court's permission to investigate the allotment of these sites. If the court agrees, Lokayukta police say other politicians and officials involved are likely to be exposed.

news.title: Pune metro line-III operation may start by year-end
news.para: With two coaches already in place, trial runs are expected to begin in Oct-Nov, following the completion of construction in Sept.

news.title: Indore: IDA unveils plans for commercial-cum-residential building in scheme 136
news.para: "The total built-up area will be 38,600 square metres, with a maximum building height of 60 metres. The estimated cost of the project is Rs 120 crore," IDA CEO RP Ahirwar said.

news.title: Mohali: Deadline for registering plots without NOCs extended
news.para: Online slots for registration had been fully booked, indicating the high demand for this service, due to which the state government took a last-minute decision to push back the deadline.

news.title: Indore administration orders FIR for developing over 11 illegal colonies
news.para: The senior administrative official said that before deciding to lodge an FIR against the colonisers, they were given a chance to present their sides, along with the required documents, in the SDM court.

news.title: Bengaluru: KG Layout site owners demand faster execution of development work
news.para: If the tender notification is any indication, the BDA is expected to complete the asphalting of roads in Nadaprabhu Kempegowda Layout only after two years. However, given the BDA’s history of seeking extensions for developmental works, there is no assurance that contractors will complete the asphalting within the stipulated 24-month timeframe.

news.title: Court sends bank New India Cooperative Bank' GM, builder to judicial custody
news.para: The accused were to be produced on Friday when their police custody was to end, but EOW sought an extension for further investigation.

news.title: Dalmia Bharat to add six MnTPA cement capacity in Maharashtra & Karnataka
news.para: The company plans to establish a 3.6 MnTPA clinker unit and a 3 MnTPA grinding unit at its existing Belgaum plant, Karnataka coupled with a new greenfield split grinding unit with a capacity of 3 MnTPA in Pune, Maharashtra.

news.title: Kolkata civic body sanctions four small plots
news.para: Mayor Firhad Hakim had asked the department to offer relief to the owners of small plots by relaxing rules so that they can build homes without taking the illegal route of not taking a sanction.

news.title: Jaipur development body earns Rs 15 crore from applications for three schemes
news.para: ​"The civic body has earned Rs 15.23 crore. The response for three residential schemes, Atal Vihar, Govind Vihar and Patel Nagar, was extraordinary. Against merely 716 residential units, the civic body has received 1.52 lakh application forms," said a JDA official.
